               <p>GRACE ROBERTS. I <rs id="t18310908-236-viclabel1209" type="occupation">keep a coffee-shop</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18310908-236-victim1743 t18310908-236-viclabel1209"></join>, in <placeName id="t18310908-236-crimeloc1210">Widegate-street, Bishopsgate</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18310908-236-crimeloc1210" type="placeName" value="Widegate-street, Bishopsgate"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18310908-236-crimeloc1210" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18310908-236-off1207 t18310908-236-crimeloc1210"></join>. On the 1st of September the prisoner came and I trusted her with bread, butter, and coffee, which came to 6d.; she came again on the 2nd, and asked me to trust her again which I did - and when she was gone I missed my shawl; she was taken at twelve o'clock the same night.</p>
               <p>CHARLES STILL. I am in the employ of Mr. Wood, a pawnbroker, in Union-street East, Spitalfields. I produce a shawl, which I took in of the prisoner.(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I had been drinking and did not know what I was doing; I pawned the shawl to get me a lodging, thinking it was my own.</p>
